ABUJA – Aide to Rotimi Amaechi, Minister of Transpor­tation aide, Dr. Israel Ibeleme, has given schol­arship to three students from the Hope of Survival Orphanage Home, Abuja. The gesture, according to him, was part of his ac­tivities to mark his birth­day on January 7, 2022. Speaking at the or­phanage home, Ibeleme, who is also the chief executive of the Israel Ibeleme foundation, said there was no better way to celebrate his birthday than to share and reach out to the less privileged in the society. 2023: Sanusi Urges Nigerians To Get Voters Card, Elect Competent… BREAKING: Diesel Tanker Tumbles, Spills Content According to him, “I have been doing this for 14 years now and I have rea­son to regret celebrating with the less privileged. “This year, I am going to give scholarship to three students from the Hope Survival orphanage home. This is in addition to other food items we have brought here today. “I feel indebted to God to give back to the soci­ety because I was once in similar situation. I also pledge to continue assist­ing this orphanage in any little way I can.”